b></div><div class="quotecontent">Coincedentally enough, I just finished my scrolling engine, which I'm so happy about, because I can now use it on pretty much any game, as long as I use vertical mirroring. Now I need to start thinking about the level engine and what-not.</div>
<br />Great! Let us see when you have something nice, OK? I guess my game is basically a level map with objects in it. Even the camera is like an object, one that is responsible for displaying the level map and the other objects. So my scrolling engine is actually the camera object. When I have it done, it's just a matter of programming all the other objects (including the player). But they are all just objects.

		

